Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and must help usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume: Ichigo needs some help his latest battle.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 46
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: Ichigo Kurosaki sees dead people and must help usher them safely into the afterlife. In this volume: Ichigo gets more training in his abilities from his father.
Title: BLEACH, VOL. 47
Author: Tite Kubo

Description: Monkey D. Luffy and his motley crew of would-be pirates search for a legendary treasure called “One Piece.”
Title: ONE PIECE, VOL. 64
Author: Eiichiro Oda

Description: This series is about grade-school boys who want to become professionals in the manga industry.
Title: BAKUMAN, VOL. 14
Author: Tsugumi Ohba

Description: Chi, a kitten with a nose for adventure, learns the different between the life of a house cat and one of a stray.
Title: CHI'S SWEET HOME, VOL. 9
Author: Konami Kanata

Description: The godfather of manga presents a murder mystery, set in the 1930’s, involving a Japanese reporter and the lives of three Adolfs, including Hitler.
Title: MESSAGE TO ADOLF, VOL.  1
Author: Osamu Tezuka

Description: In a distant future, the government decides to ban books and the libraries have formed their own group to defend their collections.
Title: LIBRARY WARS: LOVE AND WAR, VOL. 8
Author: Kiiro Yumi

Description: Lydia Carlton, who is interested in fairy lore, meets Edgar, who is seeking a mystical sword that may be his birthright.
Title: THE EARL AND THE FAIRY, VOL. 3
Author: Ayuko

Description: Asuka Masamune, one of his school's jocks, is hiding a secret. He really likes cooking, manga for girls and sewing. Will falling for Ryo Miyakozuka, the daughter of a martial artist, help him?
Title: OTOMEN, VOL. 13
Author: Aya Kanno

Description: In this reimagining of Lewis Carroll's "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland," the Cheshire Cat, disguised as a human named Boris, vies for Alice's affections.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF CLOVER: CHESHIRE CAT WALTZ, VOL. 2
Author: QuinRose
